# User avg ratings

# Cap max reviews to 3000 for better visuals
user_agg=movies_rating.groupby('userId').agg({'rating':['mean'], 'userId':['count']})
user_agg=user_agg.sort_values([('userId','count')],ascending=False)

user_agg[('userId','count')].loc[user_agg[('userId','count')]>3000] = 3000
plt.figure(figsize=(12,5))
plt.suptitle("User Deep dive",fontsize=20)
gridspec.GridSpec(1,2)
plt.subplot2grid((1,2),(0,0))

#Cumulative Distribution
ax=sns.kdeplot(user_agg[('userId','count')],shade=True,color='r')
plt.title("How many reviews does an average user give?",fontsize=15)
plt.xlabel('# of reviews given', fontsize=12)
plt.ylabel('# of users', fontsize=12)

#Cumulative Distribution
plt.subplot2grid((1,2),(0,1))
sns.distplot(user_agg[('userId','count')],
             kde_kws=dict(cumulative=True))
plt.title("Cumulative dist. of user reviews",fontsize=15)
plt.ylabel('Cumulative perc. of users', fontsize=12)
plt.xlabel('# of reviews given', fontsize=12)

plt.show()
